The '''''Journal of Literary & Cultural Disability Studies''''' is an [[academic journal]] covering cultural and especially literary representations of [[disability]], containing a wide variety of [[Textual analysis|textual analyses]] that are informed by disability theory and, by extension, experiences of disability. It was established in 2006 and launched at the Inaugural Conference of the Cultural Disability Studies Research Network, [[Liverpool John Moores University]], 2007. It moved to [[Liverpool University Press]] in 2009. 

The [[editor-in-chief]] is [[David Bolt (disability studies)|David Bolt]] ([[Liverpool Hope University]]).

